AttrDef.AttrValue: Create report only claim - caller not authorised to lodge
Insured at CSC, claim not yet lodged
Report only claim is to be lodged
New claim to be lodged by customer
Create report only claim - incident not covered
Caller validated and is authorised to lodge
Obtain policy details and validate caller (authorised to lodge)

Includes: - Obtain caller details - Obtaining Policy number from caller - Searching and retrieving Policy details from system - Validate caller is authorised to lodge a claim
NB. Further information may come from brokers via Email.
Report only claim lodged - end call

Includes: - What has happened (description of incident) - Location of incident - Loss / damage description - Injuries - Personal property damage / loss (impact points) - Police information - Requirement for towing - Driver information (licence class, involvement of drugs / alcohol) - Fraud indicators - Estimate of loss value (reserve)
- If event catastrophe code is assigned.
NB. This is done in two passes (at a high level first with detail being added through the intake process)
Create report only claim - loss outside risk currency
End call - risk / vehicle not included in policy

Includes: - Validating that the accident event is covered under the policy - Considering the impact of the driver on coverage (named driver, etc.)
NB. In some cases the caller may request that the claim is lodged even though there isn't coverage for the event. The claim is lodged as either "declined" or "WP" depending on Suncorp or GIO.
Customer requests to continue with lodgement (outside coverage)

Includes: - Determine if the policy is current / was current at time of incident - Ensuring the policy matches the vehicle involved (registration, make, model, colour) - Understanding additional benefits
Greet caller and determine reason for call
